<p><strong>Odds of winning</p></strong>

<p>The winner of the each monthly contest Round of the Evolution Games Scholarship will receive a US $1000 scholarship. There
    will only be one winner. The actual odds will depend upon the total number of eligible registered players prior
    to end of each contest. </p>
<p>A registered player can win only one monthly Evolution Game Contest per lifetime. </p>

<p><strong>How to play the contest</p></strong>

<p>GotChosen offers different games for each contest. Each player receives five tokens per day (one token is required to
    play one game). A player can choose to play five different games or use all of the five tokens to play the same game or
    any combination. Unused tokens can be used any day later in the same month.</p>
<p>If a player joins the contest after the first day of the month, the player will receive five tokens for every day missed. </p>

<p><strong>Point System</p></strong>

<p>Practice play: For each contest, players will have one practice play for each game in the contest. Practice plays
    do not use tokens and do not generate points.</p>
<p>Players can earn points in three ways:</p>
<ol>
<li>One point for each game won. A game is won if a player’s score is among the top half of the scores for that game
that day. This is considered a point-generating score.</li>
<li>One point for each different game won. Player can increase their points by winning a variety of the ten games. </li>
<li>Points earned for helpful feedback to the game developers in either the Qualifier or the Scholarship Contest.
    Players can submit feedback about the games to the developers. Players can earn a maximum of 100 points per Round
    from feedback.  Only the top 20 highest rated feedback submissions will count towards the 100 point limit.  In addition,
    only the highest feedback rating per individual game will be used.  Example:  If a player has submitted feedback for 20
    different games and all of them were rated "5 points: Very Helpful", then the player will receive 100 points for that Round.
    Developers will rate the feedback based on the table below:</li>
</ol>
<ul>
<li>0 points: Not Helpful</li>
<li>1 point:  Somewhat Helpful</li>
<li>3 points: Helpful</li>
<li>5 points: Very Helpful</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Ranking System</p></strong>

<p>The ranking system is a computer generated number that determines the position of each player and the winner of each
monthly and Championship Round. </p>

<p>The player’s rank is generated at the end of each day and the winner is determined on the last day of each Round. </p>

<p>The criteria used to generate the player’s rank are applied in the exact order below:</p>

<ol>
<li>Number of points (from the point system above)</li>
<li>Number of feedback replies from the developers to the player (not based on feedback sent or the number of points)</li>
<li>Overall position among point-generating scores for the month to date (a point-generating score is earned when the
player’s score is among the top half of the scores for that game that day)</li>
</ol>

<p>Note: The three criteria listed in the order above were designed to resolve any tie in the Rank position between
players for each game.</p>

